text: Three ships of the United States Navy have been named USS Wichita, after the city of Wichita, Kansas. * was a heavy cruiser in service from in 1939 to 1947 and active during World War II. * was a replenishment oiler in service from 1969 to 1993. * is a launched in 2016.
